    "summary": {
      "value": "Persuade enemies to retreat."
    },
    "description": "<blockquote><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Requirements:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">you must have mastered the </span><strong>Orator</strong> <span class=\"fontstyle2\">Class.</span></p></blockquote><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">During a conflict scene, you may use an action and choose a </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>soldier</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">-rank creature that can hear and understand you (the Game Master must tell you who is a valid target). If that creature is </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>shaken </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">or in </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Crisis</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, you may spend an amount of Mind Points equal to </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>【</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>20 + half that creature's level</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>】 </strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">to have them peacefully leave the conflict.</span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Describe how you convince them to desist.</span> </p>",
